      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus and yield strength sourced from certified material test reports (per ASTM F136) for the specific lot used in bench testing. Screw geometry digitised from CMM measurements (±0.005 mm). Friction coefficient (mu=0.3) from dedicated pin-on-disk tribology tests on identical surface finish. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=5000) and included in uval. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawing; traceability to device history record maintained.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-representative components with full dimensional inspection. All specimens within drawing tolerances. Device history record traceability maintained. Sample size sufficient to characterise inter-specimen variability for E/uval calculation. Required level 3 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate ASTM F1717 standard; load rate, fixture geometry, and environmental conditions documented and controlled. Multiple load levels preferred.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 standard conditions faithfully replicated at both laboratories (load rate 5 mm/min, 35 mm offset, ambient temperature). However, only a single load condition (monotonic compression-bending to failure) was applied; no cyclic or multi-rate conditions were explored. This limits the breadth of validation evidence and results in achieved level 2 against required level 3. This shortfall is noted as an open finding and does not preclude acceptance given the direct regulatory applicability of the F1717 condition."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
